// training/train_alm_14b.hexa — ALM 14B hexa-native trainer skeleton
//
// REPLACES: 2026-04-18 R37/AN13/L3-PY emergency stub (18 LOC, panic-on-entry).
// SPEC:     docs/alm_14b_hexa_port_plan_20260419.md
// STATUS:   Phase-2 structural port — CLI + dispatch + types + selftest.
//           Actual forward/backward/optim body deferred to train_alm_lora.hexa
//           (r11 real impl, 1115 LOC, already hexa-native) until full 14B
//           forward-with-lora FFI lands on hxqwen14b C side.
//
// HISTORICAL CONTEXT
//   The original trainer was training/train_alm_14b.py (264 LOC, commit
//   effa4707, last active before R37 ban). It wrote a /tmp runner and
//   exec'd `python3`. Both actions now forbidden under:
//     - shared/rules/common.json#R37
//     - shared/rules/anima.json#AN13
//     - shared/lockdown/lockdown.json#L3-PY
//     - CLAUDE.md §.py 절대 금지 (2026-04-18 강화)
//   The py source is referenced for port shape ONLY (never copied into
//   strings; never restored). See docs plan §"Reference recovery".
//
// ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
//   Base model : Qwen2.5-14B-Instruct (n_layer=48, d_model=5120, vocab=152064)
//   Fine-tune  : LoRA r=8/16/32/64 on q_proj,k_proj,v_proj,o_proj across 48 layers
//   Aux losses : 7 opt-in SESSION 2026-04-19 flags (default OFF, byte-identical)
//   Tokenizer  : Qwen2 BPE (152064 vocab) — FFI TODO
//   Data       : streamed JSONL corpus, chunked byte windows (pattern from
//                training/train_clm.hexa §corpus_open/window)
//   Optimizer  : AdamW fp32 master + bf16 params (pattern from
//                training/train_alm_lora.hexa::adamw_step line 672)
//   Checkpoint : atomic save + R2 rclone (training/CLAUDE.md runpod_mfs_quota)
//
// HEXA QUIRKS DEFENSE (per feedback_hexa_*)
//   - Single-file, NO `use` chain         → dodges silent-exit-at-5-imports
//   - ≤2 float fields in any returned struct → dodges struct-return corrupt
//   - No list mutation via helpers; rebind only → dodges pass-by-value aliasing
//   - No struct-field [float] list pairs  → dodges struct-list-alias corruption
//   - Every return is single-expression   → dodges multi-line return bug
//   - ASCII-only substring math           → dodges byte/char idx bug on Korean
//
// SELFTEST ENTRY
//   hexa run training/train_alm_14b.hexa --selftest
//   Exit 0, prints: config block, 7 aux flags, invariant block, slice test.
//   Must NOT start real training (any --corpus or --steps is refused with a
//   BLOCKED_FFI message until Day-2 C entries land on hxqwen14b).

